section.section:
An organization that meets the conditions of paragraph (2) of this subsection may conduct a gaming event or casino event if the organization is a bona fide:
religious organization;
fraternal organization;
civic organization, including:
a hunting organization;
a social organization; or
a sporting organization;
volunteer fire organization;
veterans' organization;
veterans' hospital;
amateur athletic organization; or
charitable organization.

An organization that conducts a gaming event or casino event under this section shall spend a majority of the net proceeds from the gaming event or casino event for the following in the county:
purposes that benefit religious purposes;
fraternal purposes;
civic purposes;
volunteer fire operations;
purposes that benefit veterans;
purposes that benefit a veterans' hospital;
purposes related to amateur athletics; or
charitable purposes.

An organization that obtains a permit may award a prize of money or merchandise using:
a paddle wheel;
a wheel of fortune;
a chance book;
bingo; or
any other gaming device except:
a card game;
a dice game; or
roulette.
